WEBVTT

00:01.084 --> 00:02.752
NARRATOR:
Previously on Chesapeake Shores:

00:02.836 --> 00:06.131
-How bad is it with Dilpher?
-There's an investigation.

00:06.214 --> 00:08.925
-You can't trust anyone these days.
MICK: Derrick Porter?

00:09.009 --> 00:11.010
-Emma Rogers.
-Trace.

00:11.094 --> 00:12.595
You're a singer-songwriter?

00:12.679 --> 00:15.890
We should go back
to Chesapeake Shores, rebuild our inn.

00:15.974 --> 00:19.561
-My play, it's not about the family.
-It's about you and Simon.

00:19.644 --> 00:20.895
Will you marry me?

00:20.979 --> 00:22.564
Kevin O'Brien...

00:22.647 --> 00:23.648
[SARAH CHUCKLES]

00:24.315 --> 00:27.777
-Abby, I never wanted to hurt you.
-I know.

00:27.861 --> 00:29.154
But I can't go back.

00:32.573 --> 00:34.325
It's perfect.

00:34.409 --> 00:35.744
[♪♪♪]

00:35.827 --> 00:36.911
Yeah.

00:36.995 --> 00:39.539
Well, maybe not perfect, but...

00:41.332 --> 00:45.211
Maybe not, but the termites are gone.
It's been tented.

00:45.295 --> 00:48.047
I think it just needs a fresh coat of paint.

00:48.131 --> 00:52.343
Yeah, a fresh coat of paint,
and maybe a...

00:52.427 --> 00:54.345
-A really good cleaning.
-Yes.

00:54.429 --> 00:58.600
A really, really, really good cleaning.

00:58.683 --> 01:01.102
Okay, maybe this was fate.

01:01.186 --> 01:03.188
Maybe this was meant to happen.

01:03.271 --> 01:07.442
Maybe this was some crazy life lesson,
and we're gonna reopen the inn,

01:07.525 --> 01:12.447
and it's all gonna be better
than it was before.

01:12.530 --> 01:15.241
Yeah, I don't think
termite damage works like that.

01:16.409 --> 01:19.162
Okay. Maybe we'll use two coats of paint.

01:20.538 --> 01:23.166
God, you've really thought
of everything, haven't--?

01:26.878 --> 01:29.506
Maybe we can ask my dad for help.

01:29.589 --> 01:31.216
Yeah.

01:31.299 --> 01:32.383
Or learn how to duck.

01:34.469 --> 01:35.345
[GROANS]

01:36.304 --> 01:37.430
It's gonna be okay.

01:40.058 --> 01:42.352
Oh, the curse of being a wordsmith.

01:42.435 --> 01:45.396
Luckily for you,
today, I'm having a sale on verbs.

01:45.480 --> 01:49.150
ERIN: I was hoping, this time,
it wouldn't be just words.

01:49.692 --> 01:52.237
Brilliant. What do you have in mind?

01:52.320 --> 01:55.573
ERIN:
Oh, I can think of one or two things.

01:55.657 --> 01:57.534
MARC:
I can only think of one.

01:59.536 --> 02:01.538
[♪♪♪]

02:04.457 --> 02:06.876
Lovely! And a perfect time to break.

02:06.960 --> 02:09.795
Good work, everyone.
We'll pick it up from here tomorrow.

02:10.505 --> 02:14.425
-How's it work for you, Bree?
-Um, I love it. I think it's amazing.

02:14.509 --> 02:16.594
Excuse me, Bree?

02:16.678 --> 02:19.222
Marc, it's so nice to meet you,
and great work.

02:19.305 --> 02:20.431
Oh, thank you.

02:20.515 --> 02:23.351
I just have a few minor questions
about Jace's character.

02:23.434 --> 02:26.729
I'm having a difficult time
getting inside of his head.

02:26.813 --> 02:30.692
For example, he always seems to arrive,
um, somewhat unannounced.

02:30.775 --> 02:35.155
A charming wordsmith who shows up
at the most opportune times?

02:35.238 --> 02:36.948
I like the sound of him already.

02:37.031 --> 02:38.324
[♪♪♪]

02:38.408 --> 02:41.828
-You're here.
-Mm-hm. For the last 10 minutes.

02:41.911 --> 02:44.080
I'm sorry, I don't know who you are.

02:44.164 --> 02:47.167
Oh, I believe you do,

02:47.250 --> 02:51.212
since it appears that we are me.

02:53.256 --> 02:54.257
Um...

02:55.675 --> 02:56.801
[STAMMERS]

03:00.346 --> 03:01.180
KEVIN:
Anything?

03:01.264 --> 03:02.473
[WOMAN SPEAKS
INDISTINCTLY OVER RADIO]

03:02.557 --> 03:04.976
Pulse is thready, but it's holding. Let's go.

03:05.059 --> 03:08.438
-Kev, you all right?
-Yeah, it's just-- He was my coach.

03:09.689 --> 03:12.233
-Coach Schmidt.
-O'Brien?

03:12.317 --> 03:15.278
-You want me to call anyone? Your wife?
-No. It's just me.

03:15.361 --> 03:16.446
Let's get him in.

